HEADWORD: Resupine
<hw>Re`su*pine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>resupinus</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>supinus</ets> bent
backward, supine.]</ety> <def>Lying on the back; supine; hence,
careless.</def> <rj><au>Sir K. Digby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He spake, and, downward swayed, fell <qex>resupine</qex>,⟦br⟧
With his huge neck aslant.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resupply</ent>⟦br⟧
